  description: "concurrent.futures.Future.add_done_callback co_qualname and comparison checks in cfcoq111 namespace — wave 255 theme: concurrent.futures.Future.add_done_callback.__code__.co_qualname.__eq__('Future.add_done_callback')==True (len=24: 'Future.'=7+'add_done_callback'=17=24; the longest co_qualname in this spec; co_argcount=2: self and fn — fn is the callback to invoke when the future completes); concurrent.futures.Future.add_done_callback.__code__.co_qualname.__len__()==24; compare all co_qualname lengths in this spec: done=11 < cancel=result=13 (tied) < running=14 < __init__=15 < cancelled=exception=16 (tied) < set_result=17 < set_exception=20 < add_done_callback=24 (longest); the co_qualname length ordering exactly mirrors the __qualname__ length ordering (confirmed by the fact that co_qualname==__qualname__ for module-level class methods); concurrent.futures.Future.__name__=='Future' (len=6); concurrent.futures.Future.__module__=='concurrent.futures._base' (len=24); concurrent.futures.Future.__mro__.__len__()==2 ([Future, object]); compare: add_done_callback co_qualname len=24 equals Future.__module__ len=24 (coincidental tie); the 'add_done_callback' method name (len=17) is the longest method name among all Future methods; verified with Python 3.14.3"
